    "q1_6": [
      {
        "public_status": "Public",
        "question_number": "Q1.6",
        "question_text": "Report your jurisdiction's most significant examples of collaboration with government, business, and/or civil society on climate-related issues.",
        "row_order": 1,
        "row_name": "Row 1",
        "col1_Primary entity collaborated with": "Civil society: Residents/community groups",
        "col2_Mechanisms used to collaborate": "Collaborative initiative|Knowledge or data sharing",
        "col3_Areas collaboration focused on": "Waste|Food|Energy",
        "col4_Description of collaboration and any progress, if applicable": "「チームもったいない」東京を持続可能な都市として更に発展させていくためには、一人ひとりの行動が環境全体に大きな影響をもたらすことから、「個人」の行動変容を促すことが重要です。「チームもったいない」は、幅広く様々な場面で一般消費者に対し、「もったいない」の意識を伝え、行動変容のきっかけをつくる活動に取り組む企業やNGO等の団体、個人の方々にご参加いただき、食品ロスやレジ袋の削減、省エネなどの取組や行動を通じて、個人の消費行動変えていくことを目的とした緩やかな枠組みです。チームもったいないは、次の3つの分野に関する活動を通じて、もったいないの意識を広めていきます。・食料の有効利用に関すること・資源の有効利用に関すること・エネルギーの有効利用に関することhttps://www.kankyo.metro.tokyo.lg.jp/policy_others/team_mottainai/gaiyo/about.htmlEstablishment of Team MOTTAINAIFor the development　of　Tokyo　to　be　an　environmentally　sustainable　city,　it　is　important　to　encourage citizens to change their individual behaviors considering that individual activities may result consequently in the significant influence on the total environment. In August 2018, TMG created a Team Mottainai in partnership with businesses, NGOs and other organizations. The Japanese word “mottainai” has the sense that something is too precious to waste and also expresses respect for the Earth's resources. This Team aims, through the activities in the following three areas, at raising awareness of individual consumers of the sense of “MOTTAINAI” so to change their consumption behaviors.- Saving Food- Saving Materials- Saving Energy\\nhttps://www.kankyo.metro.tokyo.lg.jp/policy_others/team_mottainai/gaiyo/about/",
        "col5_Other entities collaborated with": "Residents/community groups|NGO and associations|Local government within country/area|Climate initiatives/networks"
      },
      {
        "public_status": "Public",
        "question_number": "Q1.6",
        "question_text": "Report your jurisdiction's most significant examples of collaboration with government, business, and/or civil society on climate-related issues.",
        "row_order": 2,
        "row_name": "Row 2",
        "col1_Primary entity collaborated with": "Business: Food & Beverage",
        "col2_Mechanisms used to collaborate": "Knowledge or data sharing|City business partnership platform|Convening industry groups|Collaborative initiative",
        "col3_Areas collaboration focused on": "Waste|Social Services|Natural environment|Food|Emissions reduction",
        "col4_Description of collaboration and any progress, if applicable": "東京都は、食品ロスの削減は喫緊の課題であると捉え、2030 年の食品ロス半減を目指し、製造、卸、小売、外食の各関係団体、消費者団体、有識者が一堂に会して対策の検討を行い、連携・協働を進めていくことを目的とした「東京都食品ロス削減パートナーシップ会議」を2017 年9 月に設置した。以降、賞味期限の長い加工食品や外食産業等の食品ロス削減策について議論を重ねるとともに、キャンペーンなどの機会を通じて、事業者の取組の発信や消費者への普及啓発について、協働して取組を進めてきた。2020 年11 月の第10 回パートナーシップ会議では、コロナ禍の状況変化も踏まえた各主体の取組の方向性として「食品ロス削減に向けた提言」が取りまとめられ、都はこの提言を踏まえて、食品ロス削減推進法に基づく「東京都食品ロス削減推進計画」を策定した。\\nConsidering reducing food waste as an urgent issue and aiming to halve food waste by 2030, in September 2017 TMG established the Tokyo Food Waste Reduction Partnership Council where organizations related to manufacturing, wholesale, retail, and restaurants, consumer groups, and experts gather to discuss countermeasures and promote cooperation and collaboration. Since then, we have discussed measures to reduce the waste of processed foods with longer best-by dates and food waste in the food service industry, and made collaborative efforts in providing information on actions taken by businesses and raising consumer awareness through campaigns and other opportunities. At the 10th Partnership Council in November 2020, the Proposals for Reducing Food Waste were adopted as the direction of efforts made by the participants in light of changes in the situation surrounding COVID-19. In response to the proposals, TMG formulated the Tokyo Food Waste Reduction Promotion Plan based on the Food Loss Reduction Promotion Act.",
        "col5_Other entities collaborated with": "Climate initiatives/networks|Residents/community groups|NGO and associations|Local government within country/area"
      }
    ],
