        "public_status": "Public",
        "question_number": "Q2.2",
        "question_text": "Provide details on the most significant climate hazards faced by your jurisdiction.",
        "row_order": 1,
        "row_name": "Row 1",
        "col1_Climate-related hazards^": "Other: Air pollution　大気汚染",
        "col2_Vulnerable population groups most exposed": "Other: Any population group associated with the climate hazard will be severely affected. 気候ハザードに関係するあらゆる人口集団が重大な影響を受ける。",
        "col3_Sectors most exposed^": "Other: All sectors involved in the climate hazard will be severely affected. 気候ハザードに関係するあらゆるセクターが重大な影響を受ける。",
        "col4_Describe the impacts on vulnerable populations and sectors": "Combined impacts of Global warming and Air pollution \\nWith regard to the combined impacts of global warming and air pollution, it has been reported that the concentration of various pollutants has changed due to the promotion of the formation reaction by the temperature rise, there is a risk of increased health damage due to rising concentrations of Fine particulate matter (PM2.5) and photochemical oxidants. (Tokyo Climate Change Adaptation Plan P41)\\n温暖化と大気汚染の複合影響 \\n地球温暖化と大気汚染の複合影響について、気温上昇による生成反応の促進等により、様々な汚染物質の濃度が変化していることが報告されており、微小粒子状物質 （ PM 2.5） や光化学オキシダント 濃度上昇に伴う 健康被害が増加するおそれがあります。（東京都気候変動適応計画P41）\\n",
        "col5_Proportion of the population exposed to the hazard": "Data is not available",
