        "question_text": "Provide details on the most significant climate hazards faced by your jurisdiction.",
        "row_order": 8,
        "row_name": "Row 8",
        "col1_Climate-related hazards^": "Infectious disease",
        "col2_Vulnerable population groups most exposed": "Other: Any population group associated with the climate hazard will be severely affected. 気候ハザードに関係するあらゆる人口集団が重大な影響を受ける。",
        "col3_Sectors most exposed^": "Other: All sectors involved in the climate hazard will be severely affected. 気候ハザードに関係するあらゆるセクターが重大な影響を受ける。",
        "col4_Describe the impacts on vulnerable populations and sectors": "Infections etc. \\nRising temperatures and changes in space-time distribution of precipitation due to climate change may alter the distribution range and activity period of arthropods (such as mosquitoes) that transmit infectious diseases and the rate of invasion and colonization by non-native species that cause human damage, thereby increasing the risk of arthropods transmit infectious diseases. (Tokyo Climate Change Adaptation Plan P41)\\n感染症等 \\n気候変動による気温の上昇や降水の時空間分布の変化は、感染症を媒介する節足動物（蚊など）の分布可能域や活動期間、人的被害を及ぼす外来生物の侵入・定着率を変化させ、節足動物が媒介する感染症等のリスクを増加させる可能性があります。（東京都気候変動適応計画P41）\\n",
        "col5_Proportion of the population exposed to the hazard": "Data is not available",
