        "col7_Plan status/progress towards plan": "Underway - moderate progress made",
        "col8_Funding sources and financial instruments to finance plan": "Regional funds and programmes|Jurisdiction's own resources",
        "col9_Communities and organizations engaged": "Vulnerable population groups|Business and private sector|Citizens|Local government (s) and/or agencies",
        "col10_Describe if and how climate-related scenarios have informed the plan": "IPCC（気候変動に関する政府間パネル）「1.5℃特別報告書」では、世界の平均気温の上昇を1.5℃に抑えるためには、世界のCO2排出量を2050年までに実質ゼロ、2030年までに約半減させることが必要であり、このために、エネルギー、都市、インフラ及び産業システムにおける、急速かつ広範囲の移行が必要としています。世界では脱炭素化に向けて、目標の引き上げや、先駆的な施策の展開など、競い合うように気候変動対策を進めています。東京都は、気温上昇を1.5℃に抑えることを追求し、 2050年までに、世界のCO2排出実質ゼロに貢献する「ゼロエミッション東京」の実現を目指すため、2019年12月に「ゼロエミッション東京戦略」を策定・公表しました。（ゼロエミッション東京戦略2020 Update & Report　P11)\\nAccording to the Special Report of IPCC (Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change), limiting the rise in global average temperature to 1.5°C requires global CO2 emissions to be approximately halved by 2030 and net zero by 2050, which, in turn, requires a rapid and extensive transition to net zero in energy, urban, infrastructure, and industrial systems. Many nations are competing with each other to promote climate change measures toward decarbonization by raising targets or developing pioneering initiatives. (Zero Emission Tokyo Strategy 2020 Update & Report P11)",
        "col11_Primary author(s) of plan^": "Dedicated team within jurisdiction|Relevant department within jurisdiction",
        "col12_Assessment of co-benefits, trade-offs, and synergies of actions included in plan": "Plan assesses co-benefits of actions",
        "col13_Year of formal approval of plan^": 2019.0,
        "col16_Sectors covered by action plan": "Forestry|Sewerage, wastewater management and remediation activities|Fishing|Real estate activities|Human health and social work activities|Electricity, gas, steam and air conditioning supply|Education|Professional, scientific and technical activities|Construction|Waste management|Mining and quarrying|Information and communication|Financial and insurance activities|Arts, entertainment and recreation|Water supply|Public administration and defence; compulsory social security|Transportation and storage|Conservation|Accommodation and food service activities|Manufacturing|Agriculture|Wholesale and retail trade; repair of motor vehicles and motorcycles|Administrative and support service activities"
