        "col3_Provide a link, if applicable, and highlight any specific action the jurisdiction is implementing to reduce emissions from the consumption of goods and services in this category": "東京都資源循環・廃棄物処理計画\\nhttps://www.kankyo.metro.tokyo.lg.jp/documents/d/kankyo/resource-waste_treatment-files-r3-cwplan\\n\\n資源ロスの更なる削減（3Rの推進）\\nhttps://www.kankyo.metro.tokyo.lg.jp/documents/d/kankyo/zeroemission_tokyo-strategy_2020update-files-zero_emission_tokyo_2020update_report\\n\\n都は一般廃棄物のリサイクル率を2030年までに37%、2050年までに持続可能な資源利用の定着という目標を掲げ、この目標達成のために以下の取り組みを加速・強化している\\n1) AI・ICT技術などを活用した資源の有効利用の仕組みづくり\\n2) 再生資源の循環的な利用促進\\n3) 電子マニュフェストの普及拡大等の電子化による事務処理の非接触・合理化の推進\\n\\nTokyo Resource and Waste Management Plan\\nhttps://www.kankyo.metro.tokyo.lg.jp/documents/d/kankyo/resource-waste_treatment-files-r3-cwplan\\nFurther reduction of resource waste (promotion of 3Rs)\\nhttps://www.kankyo.metro.tokyo.lg.jp/documents/d/kankyo/zeroemission_tokyo-strategy_2020update-files-zero_emission_tokyo_2020update_report　\\n\\nTMG has set goals of increasing the recycling rate of municipal solid waste to 37% by 2030 and establishing the sustainable use of resources by 2050, accelerating and strengthening the following efforts to achieve these goals.\\n1) Creating a mechanism for the effective use of resources utilizing AI/ICT technologies\\n2) Promoting the circular use of recycled resources\\n3) Promoting contactless, streamlined office work through digitization by for example expanding the use of electronic manifests\\n"
