      {
        "public_status": "Public",
        "question_number": "Q1.4",
        "question_text": "Report how your jurisdiction assesses the wider environmental, social, and economic opportunities and benefits of climate action.",
        "row_order": 1,
        "row_name": "Response",
        "col1_Does the jurisdiction assess the wider opportunities/benefits of climate action?": "Yes, wider opportunities/benefits are assessed for many climate actions",
        "col2_Outline how your jurisdiction assesses the impact of these wider opportunities/benefits": "Wider opportunities/benefits are qualitatively assessed|Wider opportunities/benefits are considered at the action planning stage|Wider opportunities/benefits are considered at the post-implementation monitoring and evaluation stage|Wider opportunities/benefits are quantitatively assessed|Wider opportunities/benefits are considered at the action implementation stage",
        "col3_Describe the wider opportunities/benefits of climate action the jurisdiction has identified": "例えば太陽光・蓄電池や照明のLED化については、設置に係る費用と法定耐用年数間のエネルギーの消費量、料金及びCO2排出量の削減を、計画段階から評価しています。",
        "col4_Outline if and how your jurisdiction ensures the equitable distribution of climate action opportunities/benefits": "Yes, the jurisdiction is designing or implementing climate actions that address the needs of frontline communities most impacted by climate change|Yes, the jurisdiction is collecting disaggregated or spatial data to inform the design and/or monitor the implementation of climate actions|Yes, the jurisdiction undertakes wider benefits and/or equity assessments for its climate actions|Yes, the jurisdiction is engaging with frontline communities most impacted by climate change|Yes, the jurisdiction is collecting disaggregated or spatial data on the impact of climate actions",
        "col5_Outline how your jurisdiction quantifies the equitable and inclusive distribution of climate action": "市の補助によって設置された住宅用太陽光・蓄電池\\nについては、当該住宅における電力使用量とそれに伴うCO2排出量の削減とともに、売電により他の市民や事業者に供給される太陽光電力量とそれによるCO2削減量を把握しています。また市施設に設置された住宅用太陽光・蓄電池、LED照明などによる電力使用量の削減とそれに伴うCO2排出量の削減を把握しています。これらはいずれも市域の市民全体に公平かつ包摂的なCO2削減をもたらしています。\\n",
        "col6_Provide evidence and/or more details on the actions your jurisdiction is taking to ensure equitable and inclusive distribution of climate action": "幅広い市民に住宅用太陽光・蓄電池の設置を補助することで、当該家庭の系統電力からの需要量を削減すると共に、系統電力への売電量を増加しています。この結果として、設置した家庭のみでなくそれ以外の市域の家庭や事業者においても、電力由来のCO2が削減されています。また公共施設への太陽光・蓄電池の設置や照明のLED化により、公共空間における脱炭素化が進むことで、全ての市民が恩恵を受けます。"
      }
